5:
What's wrong? Does your tummy
hurt?
9:
Somewhere in the sky, there's a
huge dragon flying around!
10:
But the clouds always hide it, so no
one can see it...
15: But I didn't tell you the best part yet!
17:
The dragon's super big! And it lives
in rain clouds, where it's all rainy and
windy—
25:
...So that's how the dragon came to
be. Oh, I feel like such a fool!
27:
Her creativity was always far
beyond mine, even in the very
beginning. I'm the one who has
catching up to do...
30:
No wonder our paintings looked the
same. We painted them from the
same story.
33:
Well, the weather's nice
today—perfect for some painting.
39:
Never expected Gramp Zigza to
throw an actual festival... No wonder
we couldn't find him. He must've
been setting this up.
42:
Suizen probably tried to stop him, I
bet.
45:
But that old man can be more
stubborn than a dragon.
48:
Haha... You might be right about
that...
56:
Eh, Stella has the right idea. No more
dragon, no more danger... Might as
well kick back!
61:
I-I suppose so! We do deserve a
break after everything that's
happened.
67:
SHOW THYSELF! Or else Princess
Inaba is MINE!
72:
Here I am. I hope you are prepared
for a fight!
76:
This play adaptation of KoiAzu is
way more intense than I thought it'd
be. They even got Soushiro to join in!
82:
The samurai lad offered a hand, you
see. Wanted to help out of the
goodness of his heart.
84:
Knew right then and there that he'd
be the perfect main character!
Especially since he's so good lookin'!
88:
Well that certainly explains how he
got wrapped up in the play!
90:
I was in town visiting Izumi on minor
business, when I heard about the
festivities.
93:
Of course, with the way the Diviners'
Commission is, I am helping out in a
purely "unofficial" capacity.
98:
The play was a huge success thanks
to you! Now we are one step closer
to making this world a better place
for yokai-kind!
102:
With this, volume 2 of the
encyclopedia is gonna sell like hot
cakes!
107:
Battling in front of a huge crowd is
definitely an effective publicity
stunt...
111:
All the more reason Kugui needs to
win and make sure the next volume
is safe...
116:
What are you worried for? Have faith
in your friend!
120:
How is the competition proceeding,
by the way?
125:
It's moving along... But how it's
gonna end will depend on the lass
and you lot.
128:
Why don't we head over? It's about
time for the final showdown—and
for your company of heroes to
appear.
132:
Huh? Wait, what? I don't like where
this is going!
140:
Oh, Master! I'm just about done,
actually!
144: You. Bring your painting to life.
152:
More fun that way! I even brought it
some playmates!
157: Hold on, I didn't agree to this!
162:
Save your breath, Alk. I don't think
we're getting out of it.
167: *sigh* Your master is a real handful.
171:
Ahaha... Sorry, once he gets an idea
in his head, he won't let it go.
174:
Do you wanna animate mine too?
Think it'll even work?
178:
Generally, my power works with any
piece that looks like it could come to
life... I don't think yours should pose
a problem!
181: Since I love your art so much.
185: ...Huh? Um... Wait, did I hear you right—
191:
Here they come! Finally, we'll see
who's superior in this contest of East
versus West!
192:
Keep your eyes peeled, because you
won't want to miss it—the moment
art comes alive!
203:
Like a mighty axe, we are wood and
stone in harmony! Let us test our
bond against yours!
206:
They're talking! They're actually
TALKING! Did you just create
shikigami?!
209:
Er... It appears that way.... Perhaps I
instilled too much will in them.
212:
Well, it should be fine. We can purify
and make them your shikigami,
Ryouki.
217:
Uh, no thanks! I prefer my ogres
green!
